{{Infobox figure skater |name= Natasha Kuchiki |image= Kuchiki_and_Sand.jpg |caption= Todd Sand and Natasha Kuchiki |country= [[United States]] |birth_date= |residence= |height= |partner= [[Todd Sand]] |formerpartner= |formercoach= |skating club= |retired= |medaltemplates= <!-- see [[Template:MedalRelatedTemplates]] --> {{MedalCountry| the {{USA}}}} {{MedalSport | Pairs' [[Figure skating]]}} {{MedalCompetition|[[World Figure Skating Championships|World Championships]]}} {{MedalBronze| [[1991 World Figure Skating Championships|1991 Munich]]|Pairs}} }} '''Natasha Kuchiki''' is an [[United States|American]] [[pairs figure skater]]. Her parents, Denise and Sashi, were competitive figure skaters who met in the Ice Capades.<ref>''Skating'' Magazine, Oct. 1990</ref> Her sister Tamara was also a competitive figure skater.
Kuchiki won the bronze medal at the 1991 [[World Figure Skating Championship]] with partner [[Todd Sand]]. Their partnership ended in 1992. She then teamed up with [[Rocky Marval]], with whom she finished fourth at the 1994 [[U. S. National Figure Skating Championship]]. She is currently on tour with [[Disney on Ice]] as a Principal skater, Mulanic in the "100 Years of Magic" show.
